serverless framework in local:
  https://newrelic.com/blog/best-practices/create-a-serverless-function-in-python

  Configuring Serverless framework to Validation Account:

  Prerequisites: 
      1. gimme-aws-creds installed and set up completed
         if not follow
         https://wiki.mynmg.com/pages/viewpage.action?spaceKey=CLOUDCOE&title=AWS-CLI+using+OKta+-+gimme-aws-creds
      2. serverless framework installed
          if not follow 
          https://www.serverless.com/framework/docs/providers/aws/guide/installation/


  # get aws Config using gimme-aws-creds
  $ gimme-aws-creds --profile nmg-validation
      #enter windows credentials.
      #it will auto generate the aws config details in the .aws/credentials file

  # deploying to serverless
  $ sls deploy --aws-profile arn:aws:iam::841123234308:role/AWS-PE_USER

  Sample Project: 
  $ mkdir ~/my-serverless-project
  $ cd ~/my-serverless-project
  $ sls create -n my-serverless-project -t aws-python3
  $ sls deploy --aws-profile arn:aws:iam::841123234308:role/AWS-PE_USER
